# 31  ETHOS Hardware Setup

#### 31 ETHOS Hardware Setup

The logger has interfaces on both sides. On the front side we find power, PC interfaces, USB
and the RJ45 8 Ethernet (1 GbE), and 1 SFP+ (10 GbE) inputs. The detailed pin assignment for
each input connector is indicated in section "Hardware Information" on page 1373 .

Figure 31.1 - ETHOS connector overview.

#### 31.1 Power Supply And PC Interface

The interface to the PC and power supply is also in the frond side.

Figure 31.2 - PC and power supply interface.

#### 31.2 CAN, LIN, DIO, Analog, Kl 15

There are 2 (black and white) multi pin input connectors. With the dedicated splitter cables the
CAN FD, LIN, Digital IO and Analog inputs can be connected.

Figure 31.3 - Connecting CAN FD, LIN, Digital IO and Analog inputs to your setup.

#### 31.3 DRIVEview Display

Based on the IPEmotion ME app application a dedicated LINUX based 7 inch touch display is
available. This touch display covers most of the ME app features (exception: Audio Memos and
e-mail functionality. The DRIVEview display is supported for the following logger models:

▶ IPElog2

▶ M-LOG V3

▶ ETHOS

▶ ARCOS 1.5

▶ ARCOS 2

For the ETHOS, ARCOS 1.5 and ARCOS 2 logger a direct cable connection from FEATURE 1
and FEATURE 2 connector on the rear side of the logger is provided.

Figure 31.5 - Logger: example ETHOS
